<paragraph blockId="98.[151,1437,152,1338]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis box="[198,301,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is known only from the male and keys out easily. Sternum II lacks a pit filled with setae, while the pygidium possesses an apical fringe of setae. The mesonotum is clothed with conspicuous golden setae, while the rest of the body is clothed with yellow/white setae. The integument is entirely black.
</paragraph>
